"{\"uid\": \"sbs.com.au-news-article-from-emma-mckeon-to-patty-mills-australian-athletes-to-watch-at-the-paris-olympics-ph8t7jtyf\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Stream free online, anytime  Discover your world of SBS  Sign in or create an account  or  Stream free online, anytime  Get in touch:  Highlights around SBS:  Follow Us:  SBS acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of Country and their connections and continuous care for the skies, lands and waterways throughout Australia.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be 460 athletes representing Australia at the Paris Olympics.Source:SBS News  From 26 July to 11 August, 460 athletes will represent Australia in 33 sports at the2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 366, \"end\": 375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 470, \"end\": 479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 504, \"end\": 518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the sixth Olympics for five athletes, while 231 will be making their debut.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2024 team also has its biggest percentage of women in history, with 256 athletes (55.6 per cent) being female.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 720, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are 10 Indigenous athletes representing Australia.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From long-term stars to fan favourites and up-and-comers, here are some key athletes to watch in Paris.\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.118952347583637e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's no secret that swimming is Australia's most successful Olympic sport.\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emma McKeonis not only Australia's most decorated Olympic swimmer but the most successful Australian Olympian of all time.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.8764318906684804, \"rank\": 0.14098561959694933, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tenille_Dashwood\"}, {\"begin\": 983, \"end\": 992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1050, \"end\": 1060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999998924549858, \"rank\": 1.075344728586071e-07, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Tokyo 2020 Games, she won four gold and three bronze medals.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1150, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, she will compete individually in the 100m butterfly and relays.\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.118952347583637e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Five years after being banned from the sport after unknowingly ingesting a prohibited substance, many eyes will be onShayna Jack, who will be representing Australia for her first Olympics.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1350, \"end\": 1354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\", \"score\": 0.9998322540647163, \"rank\": 0.00010894947135968019, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\"}, {\"begin\": 1381, \"end\": 1390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jack has earned coveted places in the 50m and 100m individual freestyle, and will also be part of relay teams.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1416, \"end\": 1420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\", \"score\": 0.9998322540647163, \"rank\": 0.00010894947135968019, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other swimming stars to watch includeKyle Chalmers, Kaylee McKeown, Mollie O'CallaghanandAriarne Titmus, who set a world record in the 200m freestyle at the Olympic trials.\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1580, \"end\": 1594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}, {\"begin\": 1625, \"end\": 1631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"75 athletes have been selected to represent Australia in Paris, in what will be the country's second-largest contingent ever (behind the Sydney 2000 Games).\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1746, \"end\": 1755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1759, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.118952347583637e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In running events, 1,500m competitorJess Hullis in top form after breaking the Oceanian and Australian record at the Paris Diamond League athletics event on Monday and taking home the silver medal.\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1939, \"end\": 1947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oceania_Football_Confederation\", \"score\": 0.9910013137287654, \"rank\": 0.00892037912571664, \"text\": \"Oceanian\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oceania_Football_Confederation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oceania_Football_Confederation\"}, {\"begin\": 1952, \"end\": 1962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999998924549858, \"rank\": 1.075344728586071e-07, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1977, \"end\": 1982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.118952347583637e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1983, \"end\": 1997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.339250231151726e-12, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peter Bolwill again compete in the 800m after narrowly missing out on a medal at the Tokyo Olympics when he finished in fourth place.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"score\": 0.9432934930004132, \"rank\": 0.05699835169926223, \"text\": \"Peter\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"High jumperNicola Olyslagers(formerly Nicola McDermott), who took home silver in the Tokyo Olympics, will again compete in the high jump and has been in promising form in 2023 and 2024.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the pole vault,Nina Kennedy,who won gold at the 2022 Commonwealth Games and 2023 World Athletics Championships (in a tie) could be a medal contender.\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2399, \"end\": 2411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999999631131693, \"rank\": 3.688689484563472e-08, \"text\": \"Nina Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nina_Gamble_Kennedy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Matildas have become some of Australia's most popular athletes since the 2023 FIFA Women's World Cup.\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2539, \"end\": 2547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.453918502484576e-38, \"text\": \"Matildas\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2568, \"end\": 2577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2617, \"end\": 2621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_Women's_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9954381804438612, \"rank\": 0.004297281549966034, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_Women's_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA_Women's_World_Cup\"}, {\"begin\": 2630, \"end\": 2639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIS_Alpine_Ski_World_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9586607816420588, \"rank\": 0.038352087198225575, \"text\": \"World Cup\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIS_Alpine_Ski_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIS_Alpine_Ski_World_Cup\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While striker and usual captain Sam Kerr will miss the Olympics due to a ruptured anterior cruciate ligament (ACL).Steph Catleywill instead captain the side, withEmily van Egmondas vice-captain.\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2674, \"end\": 2682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kerr\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Kerr\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kerr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kerr\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In both the 2023 World Cup and the Tokyo Olympics, the Matildas finished in fourth place,and in Paris, they will be striving to make it onto the podium.\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2893, \"end\": 2901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.453918502484576e-38, \"text\": \"Matildas\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2934, \"end\": 2939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.118952347583637e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men's competition, participation is restricted to under-23 players, meaning athletes must be born on or after 1 January 2001.\", \"from\": 2992, \"to\": 3124, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia did not qualify for the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 3125, \"to\": 3173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3125, \"end\": 3134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Melissa Wuis the most experienced diver in Australia's team, and Paris will be her fifth Olympics.\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3218, \"end\": 3227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3240, \"end\": 3245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.118952347583637e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She first competed at the Olympics at just 16 years old in 2008, when she won a silver medal in the 10m synchronised diving.\", \"from\": 3274, \"to\": 3398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has won more than 60 medals since her international debut, and at the last Olympics, she won bronze in the 10m platform diving.\", \"from\": 3400, \"to\": 3531, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men's competition,Cassiel Rousseauis one to watch.\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He made his Olympic debut in Tokyo, qualifying for the final and finishing in eighth place.\", \"from\": 3591, \"to\": 3682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3620, \"end\": 3625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9962750349435023, \"rank\": 0.0037388922992491213, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won gold in the men's 10m individual at the 2022 Commonwealth Games and bronze in both the 10m men's synchronised and 10m mixed synchronised.\", \"from\": 3684, \"to\": 3828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 2023 World Championships, he won gold in the 10m platform.\", \"from\": 3829, \"to\": 3894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Tokyo Olympics, the Australian men's basketball team, the Boomers, won a bronze medal for the first time.\", \"from\": 3896, \"to\": 4008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3923, \"end\": 3933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999998924549858, \"rank\": 1.075344728586071e-07, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's team, the Opals, have won silver and bronze medals in several Olympics tournaments but were knocked out in the quarter-finals in Tokyo, and will be eager to improve on this performance.\", \"from\": 4009, \"to\": 4206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4031, \"end\": 4036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.397127243078771e-25, \"text\": \"Opals\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4150, \"end\": 4155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9962750349435023, \"rank\": 0.0037388922992491213, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three of Australia's basketballers will be competing in their fifth Olympics tournament:Patty MillsandJoe Inglesfrom the men's team, andLauren Jackson- who retired in 2016 then returned to the sport in 2022 - in the women's team.\", \"from\": 4208, \"to\": 4437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4217, \"end\": 4226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4296, \"end\": 4301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patty_and_Selma\", \"score\": 0.9999738205581606, \"rank\": 1.6586712020972096e-05, \"text\": \"Patty\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patty_and_Selma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patty_and_Selma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Tokyo Olympics, duoMariafe Artacho del SolarandTaliqua Clancytook home the silver medal and became fan favourites.\", \"from\": 4439, \"to\": 4560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They have reached the podium together 21 times, including at the Commonwealth Games, the Asian Women's Championship and the Osaka Open.\", \"from\": 4562, \"to\": 4697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4651, \"end\": 4656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.027934526548875e-18, \"text\": \"Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are several exciting athletes to watch in the boxing events.\", \"from\": 4699, \"to\": 4765, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tina Rahimiis Australia's first female Muslim Olympic boxer.\", \"from\": 4767, \"to\": 4827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4767, \"end\": 4771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Turner\", \"score\": 0.9785278964175204, \"rank\": 0.021943048867610032, \"text\": \"Tina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Turner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Turner\"}, {\"begin\": 4781, \"end\": 4790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999992073754, \"rank\": 7.900868555868302e-10, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4806, \"end\": 4812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9802071422621572, \"rank\": 0.020139541220573043, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won bronze in the featherweight division at the 2022 Commonwealth Games, and will be making her Olympics debut in Paris.\", \"from\": 4828, \"to\": 4952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4946, \"end\": 4951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.118952347583637e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Harry Garsidebecame a household name during the Tokyo Olympics when he took home bronze in the men's light division, and in 2024 he is striving to go even further.\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 5117, \"entities\": []}, {\"s